Sentencas: A novel perovskite-type La0.8Sr0.2Sc0.2Mn0.8O3 (LSSM) oxide was synthesized and evaluated as the electrode material of a symmetric solid-oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: A new symmetric solid-oxide fuel cell with La0.8Sr0.2Sc0.2Mn0.8O3-δ perovskite oxide as both the anode and cathode

Sentencas: Characterization was done by electrical conductivity, crystal structure stability, redox stability.
Titulo: A new symmetric solid-oxide fuel cell with La0.8Sr0.2Sc0.2Mn0.8O3-δ perovskite oxide as both the anode and cathode

Sentencas: catalytic activity for methane oxidation and oxygen electro-reduction.
Titulo: A new symmetric solid-oxide fuel cell with La0.8Sr0.2Sc0.2Mn0.8O3-δ perovskite oxide as both the anode and cathode

Sentencas: LSSM shows greater electrical conductivity than the typical La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Mn0.5O3 (LSCM) perovskite Oxide under both anode and cathode operating conditions.
Titulo: A new symmetric solid-oxide fuel cell with La0.8Sr0.2Sc0.2Mn0.8O3-δ perovskite oxide as both the anode and cathode

Sentencas: It also shows excellent chemical and Structural stability due to the backbone effect of Sc3+ for the perovskite lattice structure.
Titulo: A new symmetric solid-oxide fuel cell with La0.8Sr0.2Sc0.2Mn0.8O3-δ perovskite oxide as both the anode and cathode

Sentencas: A symmetric electrolyte-supported cell with 0.3 mm thick scandium-stabilized zirconia electrolyte and LSSM as cathode and anode shows peak power densities of 310 and 130 mW cm(2) at 900 degrees C. respectively, when operating on wet H-2 and wet CH4.
Titulo: A new symmetric solid-oxide fuel cell with La0.8Sr0.2Sc0.2Mn0.8O3-δ perovskite oxide as both the anode and cathode
